				\begin{document}$$y = at + {\mathrm{b}}$$\end{document}</tex-math><graphic position="anchor" xlink:href="41467_2019_9447_Article_Equ4.gif"/></alternatives></disp-formula>where <italic>t</italic> is year, <italic>y</italic> is single-rice harvested area or single-, double-rice yield.</p><p id="Par406">Two-linear-segments piecewise function:<disp-formula id="Equ5"><label>5</label><alternatives><mml:math><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:msub><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mo> min</mml:mo><mml:mspace width="0.25em"/><mml:mrow><mml:mo>(</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mo>)</mml:mo></mml:mrow><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:mspace width="0.25em"/><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">which</mml:mi><mml:mspace width="0.25em"/><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">is</mml:mi><mml:mspace width="0.25em"/><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">the</mml:mi><mml:mspace width="0.25em"/><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">year</mml:mi><mml:mspace width="0.25em"/><mml:mn>1985</mml:mn></mml:math><tex-math id="Equ5_TeX">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
